# TSDoc Documentation

Document all exported functions, classes, and types with TSDoc format.

## Standard Shape

```typescript
/**
 * Brief one-line description of what the function does.
 *
 * @param userId - The Clerk user ID used to scope the query
 * @param deckId - The numeric primary key of the deck
 * @returns The matching deck, or `null` if not found
 * @throws {Error} When the database query fails
 * @example
 * ```typescript
 * const deck = await getDeckByIdAndUser(42, userId);
 * if (!deck) return notFound();
 * ```
 */
export async function getDeckByIdAndUser(
  deckId: number,
  userId: string
): Promise<Deck | null> { ... }
```

## What to Document

| Export type | Requires TSDoc |
|---|---|
| Exported function / async function | ✅ Always |
| Exported Server Action | ✅ Always |
| Exported React component | ✅ Always (brief `@param props` line) |
| Exported type / interface | ✅ Always (inline property comments are fine) |
| Non-exported helpers | ⬜ Optional |

## Tags Reference

- `@param name - description` — one line per parameter
- `@returns` — what is returned (skip for `void`)
- `@throws {ErrorType}` — known error cases
- `@example` — runnable snippet in a fenced ` ```typescript ` block
- `@deprecated` — with migration note when removing APIs
- `@internal` — marks intentionally unexported helpers

## Project-Specific Patterns

### Server Actions (`src/actions/`)
```typescript
/**
 * Creates a new deck owned by the current user.
 *
 * @param title - Human-readable deck name
 * @returns The newly created deck row
 * @throws {Error} When the user is not authenticated
 */
export async function createDeck(title: string): Promise<Deck> { ... }
```

### DB Query Helpers (`src/db/queries/`)
```typescript
/**
 * Returns all decks belonging to a user, ordered by creation date descending.
 *
 * @param userId - Clerk user ID
 * @returns Array of deck rows (empty array if none exist)
 */
export async function getDecksByUser(userId: string): Promise<Deck[]> { ... }
```

### React Components
```typescript
/**
 * Renders the interactive flashcard study session UI.
 *
 * @param props.deck - The deck being studied, including its cards
 */
export function StudyClient({ deck }: StudyClientProps) { ... }
```

## Rules

- Use `/** */` (JSDoc-style) — never `//` or `/* */` for TSDoc
- Keep the first line a concise imperative sentence ("Creates…", "Returns…", "Renders…")
- Do **not** repeat type information already visible in the signature
- Run `pnpm run typecheck` after edits — zero errors required
